          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="nav-menu-btn">
          <box-icon name="menu" onclick="myMenuFunction()"></box-icon>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <p>How to use Cook Chef Assistant</p>
      <h1>Frequently Asked Question</h1>
      <!---------------------One---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          How does the Chef Assistant Work?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            The Food App utilizes advanced AI algorithms to recommend meals
            based on the type of food you have and the energy content you want
            to gain. Simply input your preferences, and the app will suggest
            delicious and nutritious options for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!---------------------Two---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          Can I customize my meal preferences in the Food App?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            Absolutely! You can customize your meal preferences by specifying
            the type of food you have available and the amount of energy content
            you wish to consume. This ensures that the recommended meals align
            perfectly with your dietary needs and preferences.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!---------------------Three---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          Are the meal recommendations suitable for specific dietary
          restrictions, such as vegetarian or gluten-free diets?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            Yes, the Food App takes into account various dietary restrictions
            and preferences. You can specify dietary requirements such as
            vegetarian, gluten-free, or any other restrictions, and the app will
            tailor its recommendations accordingly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!---------------------Four---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          How accurate are the meal recommendations provided by the Food App?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            The meal recommendations are based on a combination of nutritional
            data, food availability, and user preferences. While the app strives
            to provide accurate and relevant recommendations, individual
            preferences and tastes may vary.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!---------------------Five---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          Can I save my favorite meal recommendations for future reference?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            Yes, you can save your favorite meal recommendations within the app.
            This feature allows you to easily access and revisit your preferred
            meal options whenever you like, making meal planning even more
            convenient.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!---------------------Six---------------------->
      <div class="faq">
        <button class="accordion">
          Is the Food App available on multiple platforms?
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="pannel">
          <p>
            Yes, the Food App is available on various platforms, including iOS,
            Android, and web browsers. You can access the app from your
            smartphone, tablet, or computer, ensuring seamless integration into
            your daily routine.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!---------------------End of FAQ Items---------------------->
    </div>
    <script>
      {
        let acc = document.getElementsByClassName('accordion');
        var i;
        for (i = 0; i < acc.length; i++) {
          acc[i].addEventListener('click', function () {
            this.classList.toggle('active');
            this.parentElement.classList.toggle('active');

            var pannel = this.nextElementSibling;

            if (pannel.style.display === 'block') {
              pannel.style.display = 'none';
            } else {
              pannel.style.display = 'block';
            }
          });
        }
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
